File System App
The File System App is a command-line application that allows users to create directories, manage files within those directories, and perform various file system operations.

unarchive asmt_8.zip to your local machine:

Navigate to the project directory: cd asmt_8
Install the required dependencies: pip install -r requirements.txt
Run the application: python filesystem_app.py or from dist folder executable file.
Start the application by running filesystem_app.py

Choose one of the following options:

Create User (1): Create a new user by entering a username and password.
Login (2): Log in to the application using your username and password.
Create Directory (3): Create a new directory under the logged-in user's account.
Delete Directory (4): Delete a directory from the logged-in user's account.
Update Directory (5): Update the name of a directory.
List Directories (6): List all directories owned by the logged-in user.
Create File (7): Create a new file within a selected directory.
    note:it creates in root directory of the machine
Delete File (8): Delete a file from a selected directory.
List Files (9): List all files within a selected directory.
Exit (10): Exit the application.

Follow the prompts to interact with the application based on your chosen option.

Notes
User data, directories, and files are stored in a local SQLite database.
Each user has their own set of directories and files.
Directories and files are associated with the logged-in user.
You can log in as an existing user or create a new user.


